message.text:
There will be face-to-face MORNING CLASSES in ALL LEVELS, public and private tomorrow, March 7, 2025, Friday. 

However, to ensure that students will have a safe and balanced education amidst the persistent rise in temperature, face-to-face AFTERNOON classes are suspended, from preschool to high school (including senior high school), in PUBLIC schools in the city of Manila, tomorrow, March 7, 2025, Friday. 

Private schools and higher educational institutions may suspend afternoon face-to-face classes at their own discretion. They must ensure the safety of their students, including going to and from the institution of learning. 

According to MDRRMO’s forecast, the heat index for tomorrow, particularly in the morning (from 8:00am to 11:00am) will range from 29°C to 35°C. It is expected to rise by noon, reaching 43°C at 2:00PM.

#WalangPasok #SaHapon #WalangPasokAfternoonClasses
